    "body": "<!-- Thank you for your contribution! Please follow these guidelines to enhance your pull request. If anything is unclear, submit your PR and reach out to maintainers for assistance. Join our Slack community at https://slack.sglang.io to discuss further. -->\r\n\r\n## Motivation\r\n\r\nEnable Flashinfer-xqa for SM90 and SM120. XQA helps a lot in improving GQA performance. (Especially on H20, and also functional necessary for FP4 KV Cache fused Attention)\r\n\r\ncommand to enable XQA:\r\n```\r\npython3 sglang.launch_server ....  --decode-attention-backend trtllm_mha ....\r\n```\r\n\r\n<!-- Describe the purpose and goals of this pull request. -->\r\n\r\n## Modifications\r\n\r\n## Accuracy Tests\r\nSM120 Qwen/Qwen3.5-35B-A3B-FP8 results\r\n```\r\n# flashinfer decode backend\r\nRepeat: 4, mean: 0.836\r\nScores: ['0.828', '0.848', '0.838', '0.828']\r\n# ISL=8k, OSL=1k, concurrency=64\r\nInput token throughput (tok/s):          10955.55  \r\nOutput token throughput (tok/s):         1369.44   \r\n\r\n# XQA decode backend\r\nRepeat: 4, mean: 0.830\r\nScores: ['0.833', '0.813', '0.828', '0.843']\r\n# ISL=8k, OSL=1k, concurrency=64\r\nInput token throughput (tok/s):          10525.67  \r\nOutput token throughput (tok/s):         1315.71  \r\n```\r\n\r\nSM90 Results\r\n\r\nFA3:\r\n```\r\npython3 -m sglang.launch_server --model Qwen/Qwen3.5-35B-A3B-FP8\r\n```\r\n\r\n```\r\npython3 benchmark/gsm8k/bench_sglang.py --num-shots 8 --num-questions 1319 --parallel 200\r\nDownloading from https://raw.githubusercontent.com/openai/grade-school-math/master/grade_school_math/data/test.jsonl to /tmp/test.jsonl\r\n/tmp/test.jsonl: 732kB [00:00, 13.1MB/s]                                                                                                                                                                                                                              \r\n100%|█████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████| 1319/1319 [01:57<00:00, 11.26it/s]\r\nAccuracy: 0.895\r\nInvalid: 0.000\r\nLatency: 117.196 s\r\nOutput throughput: 1861.481 token/s\r\n```\r\n\r\nXQA:\r\n```\r\npython3 -m sglang.launch_server --model Qwen/Qwen3.5-35B-A3B-FP8 --decode-attention-backend=trtllm_mha --disable-radix-cache\r\n```\r\n\r\n```\r\npython3 benchmark/gsm8k/bench_sglang.py --num-shots 8 --num-questions 1319 --parallel 200\r\n100%|█████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████| 1319/1319 [01:59<00:00, 11.00it/s]\r\nAccuracy: 0.892\r\nInvalid: 0.000\r\nLatency: 119.940 s\r\nOutput throughput: 1812.851 token/s\r\n```\r\n\r\nNote:\r\nFor H20, XQA performs better across almost all attention backend with long ISL and large concurrency.\r\nFor SM120 and H200, XQA is not well outperformed In this case, but it's not bad, and it support NVFP4 KV Cache, which is an important feature. Here are some performance data of XQA NVFP4 KV Cache on SM120 with Qwen3.5.\r\n- BF16 KV: XQA kernel=0.72ms, decode=11.7ms\r\n- FP8 KV: XQA kernel=0.38ms, decode=8.4ms\r\n- FP8 KV: Flashinfer Attention kernel=0.371ms, decode=9.4ms\r\n- NVFP4 KV: XQA kernel=0.24ms, decode=7.1ms\r\n\r\n## Benchmarking and Profiling\r\n\r\n<!-- If this pull request impacts inference speed, provide benchmarking and profiling results. -->\r\n\r\n## Checklist\r\n\r\n- [x] Format your code according to the [Format code with pre-commit](https://docs.sglang.io/developer_guide/contribution_guide.html#format-code-with-pre-commit).\r\n- [x] Add unit tests according to the [Run and add unit tests](https://docs.sglang.io/developer_guide/contribution_guide.html#run-and-add-unit-tests).\r\n- [x] Update documentation according to [Write documentations](https://docs.sglang.io/developer_guide/contribution_guide.html#write-documentations).\r\n- [x] Provide accuracy and speed benchmark results according to [Test the accuracy](https://docs.sglang.io/developer_guide/contribution_guide.html#test-the-accuracy) and [Benchmark the speed](https://docs.sglang.io/developer_guide/contribution_guide.html#benchmark-the-speed).\r\n- [x] Follow the SGLang code style [guidance](https://docs.sglang.io/developer_guide/contribution_guide.html#code-style-guidance).\r\n\r\n## Review Process\r\n\r\n1. Ping Merge Oncalls to start the PR flow. See the [PR Merge Process](https://github.com/sgl-project/sglang/blob/main/.github/MAINTAINER.md#pull-request-merge-process).\r\n2. Get approvals from [CODEOWNERS](https://github.com/sgl-project/sglang/blob/main/.github/CODEOWNERS) and other reviewers.\r\n3. Trigger CI tests with [comments](https://docs.sglang.io/developer_guide/contribution_guide.html#how-to-trigger-ci-tests) or contact authorized users to do so.\r\n   - `/tag-run-ci-label`, `/rerun-failed-ci`, `/tag-and-rerun-ci`\r\n4. After green CI and required approvals, ask Merge Oncalls to merge.\r\n",
